Excellent — trimming redundant temporaries will make the IR and trace much cleaner 👍

Right now, every Var and IntLiteral generates a mov into a temporary.
Instead, we can make expressions return either a literal or variable name directly, and only introduce temporaries when absolutely necessary (like BinaryOp).

1. Cleaner IR Generator
integer temp_count = 0
function new_temp()
    temp_count += 1
    return sprintf("t%d",{temp_count})
end function

-- Return {ir_code, result_name_or_value}
function ast_to_ir(sequence ast)
    string tag = ast[1]
    sequence ir = {}
    object result = ""

    switch tag do
        case "Program":
            sequence decls = ast[2], body = ast[3]
            for i=1 to length(decls) do
                ir &= {{"decl", decls[i][2], decls[i][3], 0}}
            end for
            for i=1 to length(body) do
                sequence part = ast_to_ir(body[i])
                ir &= part[1]
            end for
            result = ""

        case "Assign":
            string varname = ast[2][2]   -- {"Var","a"}
            sequence rhs = ast_to_ir(ast[3])
            ir &= rhs[1]
            result = rhs[2]
            ir &= {{"mov", varname, result, 0}}

        case "Var":
            result = ast[2] -- just return the variable name

        case "IntLiteral":
            result = ast[2] -- just return the literal

        case "BinaryOp":
            string op = ast[2]
            sequence left = ast_to_ir(ast[3])
            sequence right = ast_to_ir(ast[4])
            ir &= left[1] & right[1]
            string lres = left[2]
            string rres = right[2]
            string t = new_temp()
            string ir_op = iff(op="+","add","???")
            ir &= {{ir_op,t,lres,rres}}
            result = t

        case else
            crash("Unknown AST tag: " & tag)
    end switch

    return {ir,result}
end function


Notice:

Var and IntLiteral don’t generate code, just return a symbolic result.

Assign consumes that symbolic result and emits a mov.

BinaryOp introduces a temporary because you need storage for the computed value.

2. Updated IR Example

Given your AST:

sequence AST = {"Program",
    {
        {"VarDecl","a","integer"},
        {"VarDecl","b","integer"},
        {"VarDecl","c","integer"}
    },
    {
        {"Assign",{"Var","a"},{"IntLiteral",1}},
        {"Assign",{"Var","b"},{"IntLiteral",2}},
        {"Assign",{"Var","c"},
            {"BinaryOp","+",{"Var","a"},{"Var","b"}}}
    }
}

sequence IR = ast_to_ir(AST)[1]
? IR
exec_ir(IR)

