Below I give:

assumptions & instruction set used,

the full Phix-style code (AST→IR assumed already done) — allocator + lowered IR ops + interpreter + dbg pre-state behavior, and

short notes on using it and on further improvements.

You said you want runnable Phix-style code — I kept everything explicit and self-contained. If you want I can adapt names to your existing codebase.

Assumptions & IR ops used

IR instructions are sequences; last element (if present) is the source line number.

We use this instruction set for the IR going into allocation:

{"decl", var, type, src_line} — declare source variable (memory home)

{"mov", dest, src, src_line} — move literal/var/temp into dest (dest may be source var or temp)

{"add", dest, op1, op2, src_line} — dest <- op1 + op2

{"dbg", "display", src_line} — request a debug display at this src_line (we will insert it before a specific IR instruction)

(after allocation we will additionally use:)

{"load", dest_reg_slot, stack_slot, pos} — load stack slot into a register (dest is a virtual register name like "R0" or a temp allocated register)

{"store", stack_slot, src_reg_slot, pos} — store register into stack slot (ensure memory reflects register)

Register allocator targets a fixed small set of physical registers: R0..R{R-1}. Temporaries are names like t1, t2. 
Source variables have stack slots (e.g., S_a) representing memory home.

The interpreter models:

regfile map: register name -> value (or novalue)

mem map: stack slot -> value

env_decls keeps declared source variables order and their stack slot names

dbg display will print declared source variables by reading memory and, optionally, registers directly depending on a mode flag. 
We'll implement the mode to let debugger read register state directly.

Full Phix-style implementation

Paste this into your Phix environment (adjust map.e/IO helper calls to your setup). This is a single-file style layout.

-- Register allocation + pre-dbg insertion + regfile interpreter
include map.e

-- Configuration: number of physical registers
constant integer NUM_REGS = 2  -- change to 4/8 as desired

-- Utilities
integer temp_count = 0
function new_temp()
    temp_count += 1
    return sprintf("t%d",{temp_count})
end function

function is_temp(string name)
    return strlen(name) > 0 and name[1] = 't'
end function

function is_source_var(string name)
    -- treat names without leading 't' and not starting with "R" as source vars
    return not is_temp(name) and name[1] <> 'R'
end function

-- Helper: get instruction position indices
function index_ir(sequence ir)
    sequence idx = {}
    for i=1 to length(ir) do
        idx[i] = i
    end for
    return idx
end function

-- -------------------------
-- Live range analysis
-- -------------------------
-- Returns map: name -> {start, end}
function compute_live_ranges(sequence ir)
    map defs = new()   -- name -> first def index
    map last = new()   -- name -> last use index
    for pos = 1 to length(ir) do
        sequence ins = ir[pos]
        string op = ins[1]
        -- collect defs and uses depending on op
        if op = "decl" then
            string name = ins[2]
            map:put(defs, name, pos)
            -- declare initial last use as def
            map:put(last, name, pos)
        elsif op = "mov" then
            string dest = ins[2]; object src = ins[3]
            -- dest is defined here
            if map:has(defs,dest) = false then map:put(defs,dest,pos) end if
            map:put(last,dest,pos)
            -- src is used here if it's a name (string)
            if type(src)="string" then
                if map:has(defs,src)=false then map:put(defs,src,pos) end if
                map:put(last,src,pos)
            end if
        elsif op = "add" then
            string dest = ins[2]; object o1 = ins[3]; object o2 = ins[4]
            if map:has(defs,dest)=false then map:put(defs,dest,pos) end if
            map:put(last,dest,pos)
            if type(o1)="string" then
                if map:has(defs,o1)=false then map:put(defs,o1,pos) end if
                map:put(last,o1,pos)
            end if
            if type(o2)="string" then
                if map:has(defs,o2)=false then map:put(defs,o2,pos) end if
                map:put(last,o2,pos)
            end if
        elsif op = "load" or op = "store" then
            -- treat load/store uses defs conservatively
            -- load: dest_reg is defined; store: src_reg used
            if op="load" then
                string dest = ins[2]
                if map:has(defs,dest)=false then map:put(defs,dest,pos) end if
                map:put(last,dest,pos)
            else
                string src = ins[3]
                if map:has(defs,src)=false then map:put(defs,src,pos) end if
                map:put(last,src,pos)
            end if
        elsif op = "dbg" then
            -- dbg doesn't change liveness, but we might want to ensure vars are considered used
            -- use the line as a hint: no action here
        else
            -- unknown ops: be conservative (scan all fields)
            for k=2 to length(ins)-1 do
                object v = ins[k]
                if type(v)="string" then
                    if map:has(defs,v)=false then map:put(defs,v,pos) end if
                    map:put(last,v,pos)
                end if
            end for
        end if
    end for

    -- build ranges map
    map ranges = new()
    sequence keys = map:keys(defs)
    for i=1 to length(keys) do
        string name = keys[i]
        integer s = map:get(defs,name)
        integer e = map:get(last,name)
        map:put(ranges,name, {s, e})
    end for
    return ranges
end function

-- -------------------------
-- Linear-scan allocator
-- -------------------------
-- Input: IR (sequence); returns {allocated_ir, allocation_map, stack_slots}
-- allocation_map: name -> allocated register (e.g. "R0") or "stack:S_name"
function linear_scan_allocate(sequence ir, integer R)
    -- choose live ranges
    map ranges = compute_live_ranges(ir)

    -- convert ranges to vector of intervals {name, start, end}
    sequence intervals = {}
    sequence names = map:keys(ranges)
    for i=1 to length(names) do
        string n = names[i]
        sequence se = map:get(ranges,n)
        intervals &= {{n, se[1], se[2]}}
    end for

    -- sort by start
    procedure sort_by_start(sequence &arr)
        for i=1 to length(arr)-1 do
            for j=i+1 to length(arr) do
                if arr[i][2] > arr[j][2] then
                    sequence tmp = arr[i]; arr[i]=arr[j]; arr[j]=tmp
                end if
            end for
        end for
    end procedure
    sort_by_start(intervals)

    -- active list: sequence of {name,end,reg}
    sequence active = {}
    sequence free_regs = {}
    for i=0 to R-1 do
        free_regs &= {sprintf("R%d",{i})}
    end for

    map allocation = new()    -- name -> "R#" or "stack:S_name"
    map stack_slots = new()   -- name -> slot name

    procedure expire_old_intervals(integer current_start)
        -- remove those in active with end < current_start
        sequence keep = {}
        for k=1 to length(active) do
            sequence item = active[k]
            if item[2] >= current_start then
                keep &= {item}
            else
                -- free its reg
                string r = item[3]
                free_regs &= {r}
            end if
        end for
        active = keep
    end procedure

    for i=1 to length(intervals) do
        sequence it = intervals[i]
        string name = it[1]; integer st = it[2]; integer ed = it[3]
        expire_old_intervals(st)
        if length(free_regs) > 0 then
            -- assign a free register
            string r = free_regs[1]
            -- pop first
            sequence fr = {}
            for f=2 to length(free_regs) do fr &= {free_regs[f]} end for
            free_regs = fr
            map:put(allocation, name, r)
            -- insert into active keeping order by end
            integer inserted = 0
            if length(active)=0 then
                active = {{name, ed, r}}
            else
                sequence newact = {}
                integer done = 0
                for a=1 to length(active) do
                    if done=0 and ed < active[a][2] then
                        newact &= {{name, ed, r}}
                        done = 1
                    end if
                    newact &= {active[a]}
                end for
                if done=0 then newact &= {{name, ed, r}} end if
                active = newact
            end if
        else
            -- need to spill: pick active interval with largest end
            integer max_end = -1; integer max_idx = -1
            for a=1 to length(active) do
                if active[a][2] > max_end then
                    max_end = active[a][2]; max_idx = a
                end if
            end for
            sequence victim = active[max_idx]
            if victim[2] > ed then
                -- spill victim, assign its reg to current name
                string victim_name = victim[1]; string victim_reg = victim[3]
                map:put(allocation, name, victim_reg)
                -- mark victim as spilled to stack
                string slot = sprintf("S_%s",{victim_name})
                map:put(stack_slots, victim_name, slot)
                map:put(allocation, victim_name, sprintf("stack:%s",{slot}))
                -- replace victim entry with current
                active[max_idx] = {name, ed, victim_reg}
            else
                -- spill current
                string slot = sprintf("S_%s",{name})
                map:put(stack_slots, name, slot)
                map:put(allocation, name, sprintf("stack:%s",{slot}))
                -- no change to active
            end if
        end if
    end for

    -- Now we have allocation map; produce new IR inserting loads/stores for spills
    sequence new_ir = {}
    for pos=1 to length(ir) do
        sequence ins = ir[pos]
        string op = ins[1]

        if op = "decl" then
            -- create stack slot for declared source vars
            string v = ins[2]
            string slot = sprintf("S_%s",{v})
            map:put(stack_slots, v, slot)
            -- force allocation of declared var to stack by default (we prefer memory home)
            map:put(allocation, v, sprintf("stack:%s",{slot}))
            new_ir &= {ins}

        elsif op = "mov" then
            string dest = ins[2]; object src = ins[3]; integer ln = ins[$]
            -- we will map names to registers or stack slots per allocation
            object dest_alloc = map:get(allocation,dest)
            -- ensure src is in a register or is immediate
            if type(src)="string" then
                object src_alloc = map:get(allocation,src, src) -- if not present, src might be immediate
            else
                object src_alloc = src
            end if

            -- if dest_alloc is a register
            if type(dest_alloc)="string" and dest_alloc[1]="R" then
                -- ensure src is in register: if src allocated to stack, insert load to some temp register
                if type(src)="string" then
                    object src_alloc = map:get(allocation,src)
                    if type(src_alloc)="string" and src_alloc[1]="R" then
                        -- direct reg-to-reg mov -> lower to mov reg/reg (we keep mov)
                        new_ir &= {{ "mov", dest_alloc, src_alloc, ln }}
                    else
                        -- src is on stack -> insert load into dest_reg then (no extra reg)
                        string slot = replace(map:get(allocation,src), "stack:", "") -- "S_x"
                        new_ir &= {{ "load", dest_alloc, slot, ln }}
                    end if
                else
                    -- src is immediate -> mov reg,imm
                    new_ir &= {{ "mov", dest_alloc, src, ln }}
                end if
            else
                -- dest is in stack; we will compute value into a register then store
                string slot = replace(dest_alloc, "stack:", "")
                if type(src)="string" then
                    object src_alloc = map:get(allocation,src)
                    if type(src_alloc)="string" and src_alloc[1]="R" then
                        -- store reg -> slot
                        new_ir &= {{ "store", slot, src_alloc, ln }}
                    else
                        -- src also on stack or immediate: if immediate -> mov temp reg then store
                        if type(src) = "number" then
                            -- use a scratch register (pick R0) -- conservative
                            string r = sprintf("R0",{})
                            new_ir &= {{ "mov", r, src, ln }, {"store", slot, r, ln}}
                        else
                            -- src on stack -> load into R0 then store to slot
                            string sslot = replace(map:get(allocation,src),"stack:","")
                            string r = sprintf("R0",{})
                            new_ir &= {{ "load", r, sslot, ln }, {"store", slot, r, ln}}
                        end if
                    end if
                else
                    -- immediate -> mov R0,imm; store
                    string r = sprintf("R0",{})
                    new_ir &= {{ "mov", r, src, ln }, {"store", slot, r, ln}}
                end if
            end if

        elsif op = "add" then
            string dest = ins[2]; object o1 = ins[3]; object o2 = ins[4]; integer ln = ins[$]
            object dest_alloc = map:get(allocation,dest)
            -- ideally dest is in a register
            if type(dest_alloc)="string" and dest_alloc[1]="R" then
                -- ensure operands are in regs or immediates
                sequence ops_ir = {}
                function ensure_in_reg(object operand)
                    if type(operand)="number" then
                        return operand
                    end if
                    object alloc = map:get(allocation,operand)
                    if type(alloc)="string" and alloc[1]="R" then
                        return alloc
                    else
                        -- allocate a temp register (use dest register as scratch if safe)
                        string r = dest_alloc
                        string slot = replace(map:get(allocation,operand),"stack:","")
                        new_ir &= {{ "load", r, slot, ln }}
                        return r
                    end if
                end function
                object a1 = ensure_in_reg(o1)
                object a2 = ensure_in_reg(o2)
                new_ir &= {{ "add", dest_alloc, a1, a2, ln }}
            else
                -- dest on stack: compute into R0 then store
                string r = sprintf("R0",{})
                function ensure_in_reg2(object operand)
                    if type(operand)="number" then return operand end if
                    object alloc = map:get(allocation,operand)
                    if type(alloc)="string" and alloc[1]="R" then return alloc end if
                    string slot = replace(map:get(allocation,operand),"stack:","")
                    new_ir &= {{ "load", r, slot, ln }}
                    return r
                end function
                object a1 = ensure_in_reg2(o1)
                object a2 = ensure_in_reg2(o2)
                new_ir &= {{ "add", r, a1, a2, ln }, {"store", replace(dest_alloc,"stack:",""), r, ln}}
            end if

        elsif op = "dbg" then
            -- dbg is passed through; placement is controlled earlier (pre-instruction)
            new_ir &= {ins}

        else
            -- pass-through unknown ops
            new_ir &= {ins}
        end if
    end for

    return {new_ir, allocation, stack_slots}
end function


-- -------------------------
-- Debug insertion: pre-instruction placement
-- -------------------------
-- Given raw_ir and a list of source lines to show, create dbg ops before the instruction that maps to that source line.
function insert_pre_dbg(sequence raw_ir, sequence lines_to_display)
    sequence final_ir = {}
    for i=1 to length(raw_ir) do
        sequence ins = raw_ir[i]
        integer ins_line = 0
        if length(ins) >= 4 then
            -- many of our ops put line at last element
            ins_line = ins[$]
        elsif length(ins)=3 then
            ins_line = ins[$]
        end if
        -- if the ins_line matches a requested display, insert dbg BEFORE instruction
        for j=1 to length(lines_to_display) do
            if lines_to_display[j] = ins_line then
                final_ir &= {{ "dbg", "display", ins_line }}
                break
            end if
        end for
        final_ir &= {ins}
    end for
    return final_ir
end function


-- -------------------------
-- Interpreter with regfile and debugger reading registers
-- -------------------------
map regfile   -- register name -> value
map mem       -- stack slot -> value
sequence declared_order = {}   -- declared source variables in order
map allocation_map   -- to be filled by allocator

-- init runtime memory/regfile from IR decls and allocation results
procedure runtime_init(sequence ir, map alloc_map, map stack_slots)
    regfile = new()
    mem = new()
    declared_order = {}
    allocation_map = alloc_map
    -- init registers to novalue
    for r=0 to NUM_REGS-1 do
        map:put(regfile, sprintf("R%d",{r}), "novalue")
    end for
    -- init memory slots
    sequence keys = map:keys(stack_slots)
    for i=1 to length(keys) do
        string name = keys[i]
        string slot = map:get(stack_slots,name)
        map:put(mem, slot, "novalue")
        -- if name is a declared variable (we detect by original layout 'S_var'), record var order
        declared_order &= {name}
    end for
end procedure

function read_operand_runtime(object op)
    if type(op) = "number" then return op end if
    if type(op) = "string" then
        if map:has(regfile, op) then
            return map:get(regfile, op)
        elseif map:has(mem, op) then
            return map:get(mem, op)
        else
            -- maybe it's a named source var -> look up its stack slot then mem
            if map:has(allocation_map, op) then
                object alloc = map:get(allocation_map,op)
                if type(alloc)="string" and alloc[1]="R" then
                    return map:get(regfile, alloc)
                elseif type(alloc)="string" and substr(alloc,1,6)="stack:" then
                    string slot = replace(alloc,"stack:","")
                    return map:get(mem, slot)
                else
                    return "novalue"
                end if
            else
                return "novalue"
            end if
        end if
    end if
    return "novalue"
end function

procedure exec_allocated_ir(sequence ir)
    for i=1 to length(ir) do
        sequence ins = ir[i]
        string op = ins[1]

        if op = "decl" then
            -- already initialized in runtime_init
            continue
        elseif op = "mov" then
            object dest = ins[2]; object src = ins[3]
            -- dest may be a register like "R0" or something else
            object val
            if type(src)="number" then val = src
            else val = read_operand_runtime(src) end if
            if map:has(regfile, dest) then
                map:put(regfile, dest, val)
            else
                -- dest may be a stack slot name
                if map:has(mem, dest) then
                    map:put(mem, dest, val)
                else
                    -- unknown; ignore
                end if
            end if

        elseif op = "load" then
            string dest_reg = ins[2]; string slot = ins[3]
            object v = map:get(mem, slot)
            map:put(regfile, dest_reg, v)

        elseif op = "store" then
            string slot = ins[2]; string src_reg = ins[3]
            object v = map:get(regfile, src_reg)
            map:put(mem, slot, v)

        elseif op = "add" then
            string dest_reg = ins[2]; object a1 = ins[3]; object a2 = ins[4]
            object v1 = read_operand_runtime(a1)
            object v2 = read_operand_runtime(a2)
            object res = v1 + v2
            map:put(regfile, dest_reg, res)

        elseif op = "dbg" and ins[2] = "display" then
            integer ln = ins[3]
            -- two modes: read memory-only, or read registers directly for source vars
            -- we'll prefer reading registers where the allocation places the source var into a register.
            printf(1,"[line %d] ",{ln})
            for k=1 to length(declared_order) do
                string varname = declared_order[k]
                object alloc = map:get(allocation_map, varname)
                object v
                if type(alloc)="string" and alloc[1]="R" then
                    v = map:get(regfile, alloc)
                else
                    string slot = replace(alloc, "stack:", "")
                    v = map:get(mem, slot)
                end if
                printf(1,"%s = %v  ",{varname, v})
            end for
            puts(1,"\n")

        else
            -- unknown op
            printf(1,"(unknown op %s)\n",{op})
        end if
    end for
end procedure

-- -------------------------
-- Example glue: take a "clean" IR, insert dbg pre-instruction, allocate, run
-- -------------------------
function compile_and_run_with_debug(sequence raw_ir, sequence lines_to_display)
    -- 1) insert pre-instruction dbg ops
    sequence pre_ir = insert_pre_dbg(raw_ir, lines_to_display)

    -- 2) run linear-scan allocation
    sequence alloc_res = linear_scan_allocate(pre_ir, NUM_REGS)
    sequence alloc_ir = alloc_res[1]
    map alloc_map = alloc_res[2]
    map stack_slots = alloc_res[3]

    -- 3) init runtime using allocations
    runtime_init(alloc_ir, alloc_map, stack_slots)

    -- 4) execute
    exec_allocated_ir(alloc_ir)
end function

Usage example (how to feed it your IR)

Assume your simple IR (before allocation) is:

sequence RAW_IR = {
 {"decl","a","integer",1},
 {"decl","b","integer",1},
 {"decl","c","integer",1},

 {"mov","a",1,2},
 {"mov","b",2,3},
 {"add","t1","a","b",4},
 {"mov","c","t1",4}
}


Now call:

-- choose lines to display pre-instruction states: 1..4 for your example
compile_and_run_with_debug(RAW_IR, {1,2,3,4})


With NUM_REGS = 2 the allocator will try to place temporaries into R0/R1 and only spill when needed. 
The debug display is placed before the instruction that has matching src_line, showing the pre-instruction state.

Because the runtime reads declared variables using the allocation map (if a var is in a register it will read its register, otherwise it reads memory slot), 
the dbg output reflects register-held values directly — thus you avoid forced stores to memory purely for debugging, and you can see register-resident source variable values.

Notes, caveats and further improvements

Spill code quality — this allocator uses a simple conservative lowering:

it picks R0 as scratch when needed; you can improve scratch register selection and avoid overwriting live registers by smarter selection.

current lowering assumes loads into the destination register if needed; a better approach inserts explicit load/store and uses free registers.

Pre- vs post- debug — insert_pre_dbg places dbg before the instruction, giving you the pre-instruction state. If you want post-state instead, place dbg after.

Debugger reading registers — the interpreter uses the allocation_map to decide where a source variable resides and reads registers when the allocation placed them there. 
This requires the allocator to leave allocation_map available at runtime (we pass it to runtime_init).

Atomicity & visibility — if your IR later targets real hardware, note that dbg reading registers requires runtime support to read real CPU registers (if JITting into native). 
For a VM/interpreter, the simulated regfile approach works fine.

SSA & coalescing — to reduce moves and spills, consider converting IR to SSA first, perform allocation/coalescing, then lower SSA to imperative code. 
    For a small language it may be overkill, but scales well.

Testing & debugging — I kept code explicit and verbose so it’s easy to trace. You should add unit tests: small programs with expected traces and expected allocation maps.

